# üèõÔ∏è AI Museum Curator ‚Äî Greek Mythology Edition

Interactive Streamlit web app combining MET Museum data with OpenAI to produce curator-level artwork analyses and hands-on interactions.

---

## Key updates in this final version
- Robust MET image loading (primaryImageSmall, primaryImage, additionalImages fallback).  
- Removed Course Materials tab (cleaner UI).  
- Added Myth Archetype Matcher (Jungian-style quiz).  
- Works & Analysis now displays structured museum-like sections (Overview, Context, Iconography, Exhibition Notes).  
- Home page includes session-only API Key input.

---

## Quick start
1. Install dependencies: `pip install -r requirements.txt`  
2. Run: `streamlit run app.py`  
3. On Home page, paste your OpenAI API Key (session-only) and Save.  
4. Go to **Greek Deities** ‚Üí choose figure ‚Üí Expand with AI (optional) ‚Üí Fetch related works.  
5. Go to **Works & Analysis** ‚Üí select artwork ‚Üí generate curator analysis.  
6. Use **Interactive Art Zone** for close-looking, style analysis, archetype quiz, and image generation.

---

## MET slide PDF (reference)
The app links to a course PDF at:  
`/mnt/data/LN_-_Art_and_Advanced_Big_Data_-_W12_-_Designing_%26_Implementing_with_AI (1).pdf`  
(If deploying publicly, include the PDF in repo or host it publicly and update the link.)

